Creating an HBBTV website that can stream an m3u8 stream requires knowledge of HTML, HBBTV standards, and XML. Below is a sample code to create a simple HBBTV website that streams an m3u8 file.

1. Create an HTML file (index.html):
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="application/vnd.hbbtv.xhtml+xml; charset=utf-8" />
  <title>HBBTV m3u8 Streaming</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="style.css" />
  <script type="text/javascript" src="script.js"></script>
</head>
<body onload="initApp();">
  <object id="video" type="video/mp4" class="video-object"></object>
  <div id="message" class="message">Press OK to start streaming</div>
</body>
</html>
```

2. Create a CSS file (style.css):
```css
html, body {
  width: 1280px;
  height: 720px;
  margin: 0;
  padding: 0;
  font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
  background-color: #000;
}

.video-object {
  width: 1280px;
  height: 720px;
  position: absolute;
  z-index: 1;
}

.message {
  width: 100%;
  position: absolute;
  bottom: 10px;
  z-index: 2;
  background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);
  color: #fff;
  font-size: 24px;
  text-align: center;
  padding: 10px;
}
```

3. Create a JavaScript file (script.js):
```javascript
const STREAM_URL = 'https://your-m3u8-stream-url.m3u8';

function initApp() {
  document.addEventListener('keydown', handleKeydown);
}

function handleKeydown(event) {
  if (event.keyCode === 13) {
    // Enter / OK key
    playStream();
  }
}

function playStream() {
  const video = document.getElementById('video');

  if (video.data && video.data.type === 'video/mpeg') {
    video.type = 'application/vnd.apple.mpegurl'; // HbbTV 2.0 version
  } else {
    video.type = 'video/mpeg'; // HbbTV 1.5 version
  }

  video.data = STREAM_URL;
  video.play(1);

  const message = document.getElementById('message');
  message.style.display = 'none';
}
```

Ensure to replace 'https://your-m3u8-stream-url.m3u8' with your actual m3u8 stream URL in the `script.js` file.

The above code creates a basic HBBTV website that has a message telling the user to press OK to start streaming. When the user presses the OK button, the video will start playing the m3u8 stream.

Keep in mind that to test the application, you will need an HBBTV-enabled device or emulator, as HBBTV applications generally do not work in standard web browsers.+

The following example demonstrates an HBBTV website containing two buttons that will allow you to switch between two m3u8 streams.

1. Create an HTML file (index.html):

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="application/vnd.hbbtv.xhtml+xml; charset=utf-8" />
  <title>HBBTV Multiple m3u8 Streams</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="style.css" />
  <script type="text/javascript" src="script.js"></script>
</head>
<body onload="initApp();">
  <div id="container">
    <object id="video" type="video/mp4" class="video-object"></object>
    <button id="stream1" class="stream-btn">Stream 1</button>
    <button id="stream2" class="stream-btn">Stream 2</button>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
```

2. Create a CSS file (style.css):

```css
html, body {
  width: 1280px;
  height: 720px;
  margin: 0;
  padding: 0;
  font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
  background-color: #000;
}

#container {
  position: relative;
}

.video-object {
  width: 1280px;
  height: 720px;
}

.stream-btn {
  position: absolute;
  bottom: 20px;
  background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);
  color: #fff;
  border: none;
  font-size: 24px;
  padding: 10px 20px;
  margin-right: 10px;
  cursor: pointer;
  z-index: 2;
}

#stream2 {
  left: 200px;
}
```

3. Create a JavaScript file (script.js):

```javascript
const STREAM_URL_1 = 'https://your-m3u8-stream-url-1.m3u8';
const STREAM_URL_2 = 'https://your-m3u8-stream-url-2.m3u8';

function initApp() {
  const stream1Btn = document.getElementById('stream1');
  const stream2Btn = document.getElementById('stream2');

  // Start with Stream 1
  playStream(STREAM_URL_1);

  stream1Btn.addEventListener('click', () => {
    playStream(STREAM_URL_1);
  });

  stream2Btn.addEventListener('click', () => {
    playStream(STREAM_URL_2);
  });
}

function playStream(url) {
  const video = document.getElementById('video');
  video.type = 'application/vnd.apple.mpegurl'; // HbbTV 2.0 version
  video.data = url;
  video.play(1);
}
```

Replace the `'https://your-m3u8-stream-url-1.m3u8'` and `'https://your-m3u8-stream-url-2.m3u8'` with the URLs of the m3u8 streams you want to use in the `script.js` file.

This code sample creates an HBBTV website with a video object and two buttons labeled "Stream 1" and "Stream 2." When clicking on these buttons, the corresponding m3u8 stream will start playing.

As with the previous example, to test the application, you will need an HBBTV-enabled device or emulator, as HBBTV applications generally do not work in standard web browsers.

