1. Create a new Android app (or use an existing one) and integrate Firebase following the instructions: [Add Firebase to your Android project](https://firebase.google.com/docs/android/setup)

2. Implement an FCM service class in your Android app to receive messages from your C# application. In this class, you will need to handle the message that contains the dial code and perform the dial operation. You can follow this guide: [Set up a Firebase Cloud Messaging client app on Android](https://firebase.google.com/docs/cloud-messaging/android/client)

3. In your C# Windows application, you will need to send a message containing the dial code to the Android app using the FCM Server API. For this, you can use the `FirebaseAdmin` NuGet package:

   a. Install the `FirebaseAdmin` NuGet package by going to Tools > NuGet Package Manager > Manage NuGet Packages for Solution, search for `FirebaseAdmin`, and install it.

   b. Initialize the `FirebaseAdmin` library with your Firebase project's credentials.

