To use a computed variable in Sass (SCSS) as a condition in a `@if` statement, you can simply declare the variable and then use it in an `@if` statement just like any other variable. Here is an example:

```
// declare variables
$width: 800px;
$max-width: 1000px;
$use-max-width: $width < $max-width; // compute condition

// use condition in an @if statement
@media screen and (max-width: $use-max-width ? $width : $max-width) {
  // styles to apply when condition is true
}
```

In this example, the `$use-max-width` variable is computed as a boolean value based on whether the `$width` variable is less than the `$max-width` variable. Then, the `@media` query uses the `$use-max-width` variable in the condition of the `@if` statement. If `$use-max-width` is true, then the query will use `$width` as the maximum width. If it is false, then `$max-width` will be used as the maximum width.

